13/04/2004
BUCHAREST, Romania -- A Romanian security guard was killed and one of his colleagues was injured when their convoy came under fire in the Iraqi town of Hilla on Monday (12 April). Both men were working for the Romanian security firm Bidepa and were protecting a local Iraqi government official.
In other news, Romania and Serbia-Montenegro will start talks on a new visa agreement Tuesday. Procedures will be simplified for businessmen and inhabitants of border areas, journalists, NGO representatives, and members of delegations travelling under various governmental agreements. (Rompres - 13/04/04; Reuters, AFP, AP - 12/04/04)
